---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Slovenia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/slovenia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Austria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/austria' },
  { title: 'Italy for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/italy' },
  { title: 'Croatia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/croatia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'sloveniaFit', header: 'Slovenia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€320-450/mo', sloveniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€380-530/mo', sloveniaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€290-420/mo', sloveniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '€270-400/mo', sloveniaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Slovenian ZZZS', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '~12.92% income', sloveniaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '€290-450', annual: '€3,480-5,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '€400-600', annual: '€4,800-7,200' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '€540-810', annual: '€6,480-9,720' },
  { category: 'Slovenian Public (ZZZS)', monthly: '~12.92% of income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Slovenian Supplementary', monthly: '€35-50', annual: '€420-600' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Slovenia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Slovenia. Alpine beauty, Ljubljana charm, excellent healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Slovenia"
  subheadline="Slovenia offers Alpine peaks, Adriatic coast, and Ljubljana's charm in one compact country—with excellent healthcare and EU membership at moderate cost."
  heroImage="/images/countries/slovenia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Slovenia</h2>
  <p>
    Slovenia packs extraordinary diversity into a small country—Julian Alps, Adriatic coast, wine regions, and the charming capital Ljubljana. It's safer and more affordable than neighboring Austria and Italy while offering similar Alpine beauty. EU and Eurozone membership provides stability.
  </p>

  <p>
    Ljubljana offers vibrant culture with excellent healthcare in a walkable city. Bled and Bohinj provide Alpine lake living. The coast (Piran, Portorož) delivers Mediterranean lifestyle. Wine country offers peaceful rural retirement with good facilities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good quality; comprehensive public system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Slovenian; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> €1,500-2,500/month; moderate by EU standards</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Alpine/Mediterranean mix; varies by region</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Full EU member (Eurozone; uses EUR)</li>
      <li><strong>Geography:</strong> Alps, Adriatic, caves, and wine in one small country</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Slovenia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Slovenia has universal public healthcare through ZZZS (Health Insurance Institute). Coverage is comprehensive, funded through mandatory contributions. Quality is good—Slovenia ranks well in European healthcare assessments. Most also carry supplementary insurance for co-pays.
  </p>

  <p>
    Ljubljana has modern hospitals including University Medical Centre. Private healthcare exists but is less developed than in some countries—public system is considered adequate. Wait times vary; some specialists have delays. Supplementary insurance (around €35-50/month) is nearly universal among residents.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Supplementary Insurance Norm</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Most Slovenian residents carry supplementary insurance (dopolnilno zavarovanje) costing €35-50/month to cover co-payments in public system. Without it, you pay 10-90% of costs depending on service. International insurance typically covers these co-pays, but understand the system structure.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Slovenia offers straightforward residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence (Financial Independence)</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient means (typically €1,000+/month) and health insurance. Apply at Slovenian embassy. Valid 1 year, renewable. Can lead to permanent residence after 5 years.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Pathway</h3>
  <p>
    Slovenia is digital-friendly. If you have remote income, this can support residence application. Requires proof of income and health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>EU/EEA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies. Register with administrative unit after 90 days. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage. Full access to Slovenian healthcare once contributing.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Slovenia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EU citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register for Slovenian coverage</li>
    <li><strong>After residence:</strong> Can join ZZZS if employed/self-employed</li>
    <li><strong>Supplementary:</strong> Nearly universal among residents for co-pays</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Slovenia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Once in Slovenian system (through employment or voluntary contribution), add local supplementary insurance for co-pays. Keep international coverage for travel and potential treatment abroad for complex conditions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Slovenia, these providers offer strong coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Slovenia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, accepted for residence</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Alpine region pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Slovenian Supplementary:</strong> Vzajemna, Triglav for local system top-up</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that accept seniors for Slovenia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Slovenia are moderate—between Eastern and Western Europe:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Join ZZZS:</strong> If eligible, public system + supplementary is cost-effective</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> €5,000+ deductible on international reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Slovenia exclusion:</strong> Once in local system, exclude from international</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Alpine region coverage can be efficient</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Nature Lover, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Loves hiking and wants Alpine lifestyle cheaper than Switzerland.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa. Settles near Bled. Register for ZZZS through voluntary contribution.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~€400/month. After ZZZS: public + supplementary ~€150/month + Cigna (Slovenia excluded) ~€250.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Italian EU Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Moving from Milan to Ljubljana. Italian pension €1,800/month. Seeks better value.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EU rights apply. Register for Slovenian healthcare. Add supplementary. Allianz for Italy visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ZZZS + supplementary ~€120/month + Allianz (Slovenia excluded) ~€250/month. Half the cost of Milan.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Coastal Seeker, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, wants Mediterranean feel at lower cost. Pension £2,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for visa. Lives in Piran on Adriatic coast. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~€480/month. Mediterranean lifestyle at fraction of Italian Riviera prices.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Slovenia compare to Austria?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Similar Alpine beauty, significantly cheaper. Slovenia's cost of living is 40-50% lower than Austria. Healthcare is good (not quite Austrian level but solid). Ljubljana is charming if smaller than Vienna. Less developed tourism infrastructure but that's part of the appeal.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Slovenian hard to learn?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Slovenian is Slavic with complex grammar—challenging for English speakers. However, English is widely spoken, especially in Ljubljana and tourist areas. Older generation may speak German. Many expats manage with English; learning basics is appreciated but not essential for daily life.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the supplementary insurance about?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Slovenian public healthcare requires co-payments (10-90% depending on service). Nearly all residents carry supplementary insurance (€35-50/month) to cover these. Vzajemna and Triglav are main providers. Without it, costs add up. International insurance typically covers full costs anyway.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I access Italy/Austria easily?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes. Slovenia borders both. Ljubljana to Venice is 2.5 hours by car. Austrian Graz is 1.5 hours. Schengen means no border controls. Many Slovenia residents enjoy Italian restaurants, Austrian shopping, or Croatian coast as day trips. Perfect central location.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that specialize in senior expat coverage for Slovenia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Slovenian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
